                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <origDate notBefore="1750" notAfter="1799" evidence="lettering"/>
                            The manuscript can be dated palaeographically to the second half of the eighteenth century. A single mention of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ንጉሥነ፡ <gap reason="lost"/>ያሱ፡</foreign>
                            on <locus target="#3r"/> might point to the reign of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5618IyasuII">ʾIyāsu III</persName> as the period of production.
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>The manuscript had very probably belonged to a church in the <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName> area, 
                            possibly <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC6539Gabreel">Gabrǝʾel</placeName>,
                            from where it was taken by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9430Tewodros">Tewodros</persName> and brought to <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0101MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</placeName>.
                            It was then looted by the British <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7484Napier">Napier</persName> expedition
                            in <date>1868</date>.</provenance>
                    </history>
                    
